The paper presents data structures for maintaining maximum cardinality and maximum weighted matchings on sparse graphs in sublinear time per update. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). However, given the focus on dynamic graph algorithms, cs.DS and cs.DM are the most likely categories. The use of approximation algorithms and trimming techniques also suggests that cs.CG and cs.GT are possible categories. Finally, the mention of worst-case time bounds and approximation ratios suggests that cs.NA is a possible category as well.
